        <h1 class="heading">Final Flight</h1>
        <p class="missing"> All of this and more before setting off on her final flight on July 2, 1937. Amelia, accompanied by navigator Fred Noonan, left from  Lae, New Guinea, headed to their next fuel stop in  Howland Island. After they did not arrive a massive sea and air search was issued only to find nothing. Amelia Mary Hartman and Fred Noonan were declared lost at sea on July 18, 1937. Amelia would be declared dead  January 5, 1939. </p>
